{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Finally, we again normalize pixel values to zero-mean/unit-variance statistics using the mean and standard deviation.",
    "For MAE pre-training we adopt similar parameters used by He et al. (2022), training for 1000 epochs with a batch size of 4096.",
    "We use the AdamW optimizer (Loshchilov & Hutter, 2017) with parameters β 1 = 0.9, β 2 = 0.95, and a weight decay of 0.05.",
    "We optimize for the learning rate, finding an optimal learning rate of 5.0 × 10 -4 for BP-MAE and 1.0 × 10 -3 for DBP-MAE (see Appendix A).",
    "We use a cosine decay learning rate scheduler (Loshchilov & Hutter, 2016) with a warmup of 40 epochs."
  ],
